Cells renew themselves starting from the crypts and migrate upward along the villi. Given that information, we know that goblet cells start near the base of the crypts and gradually spread out over the length of the villi as they mature. Thus, the correct order would show goblet cells appearing lower on the villi compared to other cell types.
\boxed{B} Based on the evidence showing that stem cells within the crypts generate various cell types including goblet cells, which then migrate upwards along the villi, goblet cells should be closer to the base of the villi rather than distributed evenly or predominantly nearer the tips.
\boxed{B}
